public class HierarchicObjectDMO
extends DmcObject
implements DmcNamedObjectIF, java.io.Serializable

A HierarchicObject is meant to represent any object that can be identified with a Fully Qualified Name (FQN) and exists in a containment relationship with other objects. The exact implementation of a HierarchicObject is application specific.
